"{\"uid\": \"pasoroblesdailynews.com-tip-a-cop-event-to-raise-funds-for-special-olympics-athletes-197164\", \"text\": \"  - ThePaso Robles Police Departmentwill host its annual \\\"Tip-A-Cop\\\" fundraiser on Sept. 18 at the Paso Robles Event Center to benefit Special Olympics Southern California. The event is part of a statewide initiative that involves law enforcement officers serving dinner to raise funds and awareness for Special Olympics athletes.  The event features two seating times, at 5:30 p.m. and 7 p.m. A table for eight is available for $250, and individual meals for pick-up are also an option for those unable to attend. All proceeds will support Special Olympics programs in San Luis Obispo County, which provide opportunities for athletes with intellectual disabilities to participate in year-round sports, health, and community activities.  For reservations, meal orders, or donations, visit the Special Olympics SLO County Tip-A-Cop page.  For more information, contact Jody Watty at Special Olympics Southern California at jwatty@sosc.org.  \\u200b\\u200b  \\u200b  \\u200b  The news staff of the Paso Robles Daily News wrote or edited this story from local contributors and press releases. The news staff can be reached at info@pasoroblesdailynews.com.  When you need reliabletree service in Paso Robles, Golden State Tree Service is your trusted local expert. With over 30 years of experience, they handle everything from emergency tree removal and stump grinding to professional pruning, trimming, and defensible space clearing. Their licensed and insured team serves Paso Robles, Atascadero, Templeton, San Luis Obispo, and all Central Coast communities with 24/7 availability and free estimates. Whether you are dealing with a fallen tree, diseased vegetation, or routine maintenance, Golden State Tree Service delivers quality results at affordable prices-leaving your property clean, safe, and beautiful.    Call (805) 835-1013 today for fast, professional service you